The paper deals with algorithmic problems on planar graphs, which are typically studied in the subfields of computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM, cs.GT). The use of sparsification techniques and kernelization algorithms suggests a focus on parameterized complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS).
